This paper discusses the design of a MAC protocol for GHz wireless local area networks (WLANs), which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization of channel utilization and link budget criteria, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and millimeter wave technology (cs.MM). The proposed algorithm also involves system optimization and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
